HEADWORD: alligatored
<hw>alligatored</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <fr>1</fr> <def>having
cracks in a reticulated pattern, giving an appearance reminiscent of
alligator hide; -- said of a surface coating, e.g., of paint, varnish,
or glazing</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> cracked</syn>⟦br⟧
